  "texts": [
    "To this end, in addition to merely representing statistical dependencies, the models should learn causal representations that support prediction under interventions and that have been argued to be more robust with respect to ubiquitous distribution shifts 106.",
    "Causal representations structure problems in terms of mechanisms underlying the datagenerating process, and lend themselves well to building hybrid models or causal digital twins that combine components learned from data with other sources of knowledge, such as surrogate models or simulations 132.",
    "This can be in conflict with the popular end-to-end learning, but it provides sequential \"checkpoints\" (e.g.",
    "prediction, then communication) which may additionally enhance model trust.",
    "Further considerations that may inform the design of those models is the level of explainability, transparency and recourse that they should provide."
